articles.title: Ukraine Issue Will Be Discussed Between PM Modi, Joe Biden: White House
articles.author: Press Trust
articles.excerpt: The Ukraine issue will come up in the discussions between Prime Minister Narendra Modi and US President Joe Biden, a White House official said.
articles.summary:
Ukraine war would be discussed during the meeting between PM Modi and Joe Biden.

Washington:

The Ukraine issue will come up in the discussions between Prime Minister Narendra Modi and US President Joe Biden, a White House official said.

National Security Council Coordinator for Strategic Communications John Kirby, however, said to what "degree specifically they will talk about a peace summit or a peace proposal, I cannot say right now".

PM Modi is visiting the US from June 21-24 at the invitation of President Joe Biden and First Lady Jill Biden, who will host him at a State Dinner on June 22.

Speaking to donors in California on Monday (19.06.23), Biden said: "When I was out here about two years ago saying I was worried about the Colorado river drying up, everybody looked at me like I was crazy.

articles.title: Endgame Biden vs Putin?
articles.author: Deepali Saxena
articles.excerpt: In 2020, Putin's most formidable opponent Joe Biden was back in the office and as no other but the President. Joe Biden brought along with him years of experience dealing with the Soviet Union and…
articles.summary:
Joe Biden and Vladimir Putin
Photo : AP
Subscribe to Notifications
The rivalry dates back to the cold war.
Both cold war warriors, Joe Biden had already made several visits to Moscow in the 1980s as a young senator from Delaware, while Putin was a freshly recruited, young-blood KGB officer who had joined the Soviet's Secret Intelligence Service in 1975, immediately after his graduation.
Putin was serving as a KGB spy in East Germany during the fall of the Berlin Wall in 1989 – making protection calls during the violent demonstrations.

articles.summary:
House Oversight Committee Chair James Comer (R-KY) said he will review  Tuesday two additional FBI documents referenced in the bureau's file that alleged the infamous bribery scheme involving President Joe Biden and a Ukrainian oligarch.


Comer said the review will take place at 4:00 p.m. and will include House Oversight Committee Ranking Member Jamie Raskin (D-MD), Fox News 
reported
.






It is unknown what additional information the documents might contain.


On June 9, Rep. Marjorie Taylor Greene (R-GA) exclusively 
told
 Breitbart News Comer and Rankin would inspect the two additional forms in the near future.

articles.title: US President Joe Biden calls China's Xi Jinping a 'dictator'
articles.author: Aman Gupta
articles.excerpt: US President Biden called Chinese President Xi Jinping a 'dictator' and stated that Xi was embarrassed when a Chinese balloon was blown off course over the US earlier this year.
articles.summary:
US President Joe Biden on Tuesday termed his Chinese counterpart Xi Jinping as a ‘dictator'. The US leader added that Xi was found embarrassed when a Chinese balloon was blown off course over the US earlier this year. 
 
 
 
 According to Reuters, Biden was speaking at a fundraiser in California when he took this sharp dig at the Chinese President. Meanwhile, US Secretary of State Anthony Blinken is on a rare visit to China in a bid to ease tensions between the two countries.
